create multi device experiences

00:00:10.720 --> 00:00:14.790
integrated with their existing
apps on Android, iOS, and the web.

00:00:15.800 --> 00:00:19.650
Android TV simply takes Android and
brings it into the living room.

00:00:19.650 --> 00:00:22.990
This makes it a deal for
extending your existing Android app

00:00:22.990 --> 00:00:27.240
to work in the living room whether or
not the user has their phone on them.

00:00:27.240 --> 00:00:31.490
You can integrate your service or
app with Google Cast, Android TV, or

00:00:31.490 --> 00:00:32.659
even better both.

00:00:34.020 --> 00:00:37.550
Where to start and how to go further
depends on the type of service and

00:00:37.550 --> 00:00:40.000
what platforms are already integrated.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:43.498
In many case you can then extend
to cover multiple platforms for

00:00:43.498 --> 00:00:44.818
the greatest impact and

00:00:44.818 --> 00:00:48.778
best user experience regardless of
what the user has driving their TV.

00:00:48.778 --> 00:00:52.810
The most common use case I hear
talked about is streaming media.

00:00:52.810 --> 00:00:57.210
Whether your app is on Android, iOS or
web your first step in building for

00:00:57.210 --> 00:01:00.510
the living room is adding in
Google Cast functionality.

